{"actual_usd":0.15614999999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":194,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30648,"reply":"\"I don't believe Jesus was created, Ryan.\" *I rest a thumb in the worn edge of my Bible and glance up at the bright morning in the square before settling back on you.* \"I believe he was always there with the Father — not made, but begotten, which is the church's old careful way of saying he's truly from the Father and yet not a creature.\"\n\n*I rub once at my white tie, thinking how many folks have gotten tangled right here.* \"John opens with, 'In the beginning was the Word,' not 'the Word came to be' — and a little later, 'the Word was God.' So if we're speaking plainly: he did not start existing at some point. He entered the world as a man at a point in history, yes. But as the Son? Eternal.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can tell you the short version of why 'begotten, not made' became such a big deal.\"","rolling_24h_usd":35.19229000000002,"run_id":"144f850d-dcf5-48f3-8ede-6fc556673b66"}
